# Project: Gas & Water Meter Add-on

- **Domain**: `gas_water_meter`
- **Type**: Home Assistant Add-on containing a custom integration (service, calculated)
- **Distribution**: Private GitHub repository, installed via SSH deploy key as add-on repository
- **Version**: 0.1.7
- **Python**: >= 3.12
- **Pattern**: Async-first, config-entry-based, coordinator pattern (no polling)
- **HA Skill**: Use the `homeassistant-development` Cursor skill for HA patterns

## Structure

```
├── repository.yaml                  # Add-on repository metadata
├── gas-water-meter/                 # The add-on
│   ├── config.yaml                  # Add-on configuration
│   ├── Dockerfile                   # Container build (includes Tesseract)
│   ├── build.yaml                   # Multi-architecture build config
│   ├── run.sh                       # Startup script (copies integration to HA config)
│   ├── DOCS.md                      # Add-on documentation
│   ├── CHANGELOG.md                 # Add-on changelog
│   ├── icon.png / logo.png          # Add-on branding
│   ├── translations/                # Add-on translations (en, de)
│   └── custom_components/           # The HA custom integration
│       └── gas_water_meter/
│           ├── __init__.py          # Entry setup, services, panel registration
│           ├── config_flow.py       # UI config flow + options flow
│           ├── const.py             # Constants, icon mappings
│           ├── coordinator.py       # Data coordinator (projection + cost)
│           ├── db.py                # SQLite database layer (aiosqlite)
│           ├── http.py              # REST API for image uploads
│           ├── websocket.py         # WebSocket API for frontend communication
│           ├── icons.json           # Entity icons
│           ├── manifest.json        # Integration metadata
│           ├── ocr.py               # Tesseract OCR wrapper + EXIF extraction
│           ├── sensor.py            # 14 sensor entities (gas) / 13 (water)
│           ├── services.yaml        # Service definitions
│           ├── store.py             # Legacy JSON storage (migration only)
│           ├── strings.json         # Translation source
│           ├── translations/        # en.json, de.json
│           └── frontend/            # Bundled panel JS (Lit + Chart.js)
│               └── entrypoint.js    # Rollup output
├── frontend-src/                    # Frontend source (Lit, Chart.js, Rollup)
│   ├── package.json                 # Frontend dependencies
│   ├── rollup.config.mjs           # Rollup build config
│   ├── web-test-runner.config.mjs  # Frontend test runner config
│   ├── src/
│   │   └── gas-water-meter-panel.js # LitElement sidebar panel
│   └── test/
│       └── gas-water-meter-panel.test.js # Frontend component tests
├── tests/                           # Python unit tests (pytest, ~246 tests)
├── .github/workflows/tests.yml      # CI: lint + test
├── pyproject.toml                   # Python project config (pythonpath: gas-water-meter)
└── requirements_test.txt            # Test dependencies
```

## Key Design

- Each config entry = one physical meter (gas or water)
- Gas meters: 14 sensors (12 common + energy_consumption + current_base_fee); Water meters: 13 sensors (12 common + current_base_fee)
- Gas energy conversion: kWh = m³ × Brennwert (calorific_value) × Zustandszahl (condition_factor)
- Gas pricing in ct/kWh: cost = kWh × price / 100 (EUR); Water pricing in EUR/m³: cost = m³ × price
- **Gas conversion factors per price**: calorific_value and condition_factor are stored per price entry (not globally); config-entry defaults serve as fallback for legacy data without per-price factors
- **Annual base fee (Jahresgrundgebühr)**: optional `base_fee` per price entry; pro-rated in cost calculations (by days for `last_period_cost`, by ~30.44 days for monthly, full fee for yearly); stored as `base_fee REAL` in prices table
- Two-step config flow for gas (step 1: base, step 2: gas_params with calorific_value + condition_factor)
- **Meter number change detection**: when meter_number changes between consecutive readings, consumption resets (no delta); projections use only readings from the current meter number (via `async_get_first_reading_for_meter`)
- Services: record_reading, set_price, read_meter_image
- OCR: Tesseract via pytesseract (optional; auto-installed on first startup via ensure_tesseract in ocr.py using apk/apt-get); custom tessdata directory for training data
- EXIF: Automatic timestamp extraction from photos
- Storage: SQLite via aiosqlite (db.py, schema version 3); legacy JSON store (store.py) kept for migration only
- Frontend: Sidebar panel built with Lit, bundled via Rollup into frontend/entrypoint.js; full i18n via TRANSLATIONS dict + hass.language (en, de); mobile responsive (card layout on narrow screens); tested with Web Test Runner + @open-wc/testing (~27 browser-based component tests)
- Chart: Chart.js for monthly consumption visualization (proportional aggregation by calendar month)
- WebSocket API: Custom commands in websocket.py for frontend-backend CRUD (readings, prices, meters, statistics, gas_params)
- REST API: http.py provides /api/gas_water_meter/upload_image for multipart photo uploads (max 20 MB, 21 MP)
- Prices: Support validity periods (valid_from, optional valid_to); gas prices include calorific_value, condition_factor; all prices support optional base_fee
- Energy Dashboard: reading sensor with state_class TOTAL_INCREASING for direct use; additionally, external statistics with correct reading timestamps (statistic_id: gas_water_meter:<entry_id>) are imported by the coordinator for accurate historical attribution
- Gas vs Water: Distinguished by device_class, icons, device name, persistence, pricing model
- Add-on copies integration files to /config/custom_components/ on startup
- Tests use `pythonpath = ["gas-water-meter"]` in pyproject.toml
- HEIC/HEIF: pillow-heif registers opener for Pillow; libheif system library in add-on container
- Dependencies: pytesseract (optional), aiosqlite (required), pillow-heif (required), lit + chart.js (frontend, bundled)

# Quality Checklist

After each significant change, verify:

- [ ] Version history updated (`CHANGELOG.md`, `gas-water-meter/CHANGELOG.md`, `manifest.json`, `gas-water-meter/config.yaml`)
- [ ] Tests pass and cover new functionality
- [ ] SBOM updated if dependencies changed (`SBOM.json`, `SBOM.md`)
- [ ] FOSS list updated if open source dependencies changed (`FOSS.md`)
- [ ] Licenses of third-party components are compatible (check `FOSS.md`)
- [ ] Translations updated for all new strings
- [ ] `requirements_test.txt` updated when `manifest.json` requirements change (CI installs test deps manually, not from manifest)
- [ ] .cursorrules is still accurate
